meta {
  name: List Lab Tests (Listing & Views)
  type: http
  seq: 6
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/master-data/{{masterDataId}}/lab-tests/listing?view=RESULTS&page=1&limit=20&search=Complete
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

params:query {
  view: RESULTS
  page: 1
  limit: 20
  search: Complete
  ~departmentId: 
  ~categoryId: 
  ~subCategoryId: 
  ~status: ACTIVE
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{businessAccessToken}}
}

vars:pre-request {
  masterDataId: 3bebbd8d-eef4-4bfa-88f3-3aff4a4a4516
}

docs {
  Configurable listing screen for a master data's lab tests. One endpoint; the
  `view` query param selects which columns (and, for the child-centric views,
  nested arrays) are projected. Paginated **by lab test** (`meta.total` always
  counts tests, even for the nested views). 404 `MASTER_DATA_NOT_FOUND` if the
  parent master data is missing/other tenant.
  
  ## Search & filters (all optional)
  
  - `search` ‚Äî matches `testName` OR `testCode` only (case-insensitive,
    `contains`). Other fields are not searched, by design.
  - `departmentId` / `categoryId` / `subCategoryId` ‚Äî filter by id. The matching
    **names** are resolved server-side and returned in the views that show them.
  - `status` ‚Äî `ACTIVE` | `INACTIVE` (maps to the `isActive` flag). Soft-deleted
    tests are always excluded regardless of `status`.
  - `page` / `limit` ‚Äî standard pagination (limit capped at 100).
  
  > The disabled (`~`) query params above are examples ‚Äî enable the ones you
  > want. Don't send an empty `status`/`view` (an empty enum value ‚Üí 400
  > `VALIDATION_ERROR`); omit them instead.
  
  ## Views (`view`)
  
  Each value projects a different row shape:
  
  - `DEFAULT` (default) ‚Äî testName, testCode, departmentName, priceMsrp,
    tatMaxValue/Unit, **defaultSample** (the `isDefault` sample), **parametersCount**, isActive.
  - `BASIC_DETAILS` ‚Äî testName, testCode, aka, departmentName, categoryName,
    subCategoryName, processMethod, approvalWorkflowId, isMandatoryTest,
    samplePriorityType, icdCode, loincCode.
  - `PRICING` ‚Äî the full price ladder (msrp/min/max/original/franchise/emergency,
    discountCapPct, isAllowPriceOverride).
  - `TAT` ‚Äî tatMin/Max (value+unit), schedule from/to, processing time min/max
    (value+unit), approval time from/to.
  - `FLAGS` ‚Äî isHideInOrderScreen, isEnableCms, isPreferenceTest, isActive.
  - `SAMPLE` ‚Äî testName, testCode, departmentName, isActive + nested `samples[]`
    (sampleNameId, containerType, sampleSize, isFastingRequired, transportTemperature).
  - `RESULTS` ‚Äî testName, testCode, departmentName, isActive + nested
    `resultParams[]` (parameterName, method, resultType, units, isNabl, isCap).
  - `REFERENCE_RANGE` ‚Äî testName, testCode + nested `referenceRanges[]`
    (parameterName, method, gender, ageFrom, ageTo, lowerLimit, upperLimit,
    displayOfReferenceRange, flag).
  - `REFERENCE_VALUE` ‚Äî testName, testCode + nested `referenceValues[]`
    (parameterName, method, gender, ageFrom, ageTo, displayValue, flag).
  - `NOTES` ‚Äî usefulFor, interpretationOfResults, limitations, remarks, references.
  - `VERSION_CONTROL` ‚Äî testName + currentVersion/effectiveFrom/modifiedBy
    (the open entry, else the highest) + the full `versionHistory`.
  - `OVERVIEW` ‚Äî testName, testCode, departmentName, maxValue (= priceMaximum),
    tatMaxValue/Unit, samplesCount, parametersCount, isActive.
  
  ## Fields mapped/omitted (no backing column yet)
  
  Some requested columns have no field on the model today, so they are mapped to
  the nearest field or omitted (to be wired when those modules land):
  
  - `FLAGS` "Reference test" ‚Üí `isPreferenceTest`; "Bill only / Disable discount
    / Outsource / Sample flow" ‚Üí omitted.
  - `TAT` "Reporting time" and extra from/to ‚Üí omitted (only schedule/processing/
    approval windows exist).
  - `BASIC_DETAILS` "Approval" ‚Üí `approvalWorkflowId` (logical ref).
  - `SAMPLE` "Sample / Sample type" ‚Üí `sampleNameId` + `containerType` (no sample
    catalogue yet, so no resolved sample name).
  - `OVERVIEW` "Max value" ‚Üí `priceMaximum`.
  
  This endpoint is read-only and additive ‚Äî the original `List Lab Tests`
  (core rows only) is unchanged.
}
